            "title": "Aaron Levie · @levie · CEO, Box",
            "text": "🔗 Post — Enterprise AI agents · 🔗 Post — Enterprise data After meetings with dozens of enterprise IT leaders, Levie reports the dominant blocker: AI's full value requires solving an operating model challenge first. Most organizations run legacy siloed structures (separate IT, finance, ops) where AI value lives in the handoffs across those siloes, not within a single function. In a second post, he notes that most of the data AI needs lives inside organizations — in legacy systems, people's heads, fragmented acros…",
