            "title": "Training Data — \"Why Hardware-Software Co-Design Is AI's Real 100x: Dylan Patel of SemiAnalysis\"",
            "text": "[🔗 · Published 2026-07-02 Guest: Dylan Patel, Founder & CEO, SemiAnalysis · Hosts: Sean & Sonja Huang (Sequoia) Core Argument / 核心论点 The biggest efficiency gains in AI don't come from optimizing any single layer of the stack — not hardware alone, not kernel software, not model architecture — but from co-designing all three together. A 2x gain on each layer gives 8x multiplicative improvement, but true cross-layer co-optimization can produce 100x, because constraints at one layer can be relaxed when another layer …",
