            "text": "🔗 Post Rauch coined the sharpest line of the day: \"Coding agents will squeeze every ounce of IKEA effect out of you, if you let them.\" The IKEA effect — the cognitive bias where people overvalue things they've assembled themselves — is a real psychological trap in agentic workflows. Letting the agent do everything feels efficient but strips away the ownership and judgment that makes you a better builder over time. The implication: intentional, selective use of coding agents, where you stay in the loop on the part…",
