            "text": "The Core Argument LLMs are not a path toward human-level or even animal-level intelligence. They are excellent tools for language manipulation — and that domain is genuinely large and valuable — but they fundamentally cannot predict the consequences of their own actions, cannot plan by search and optimization, and cannot generalize to novel tasks zero-shot. These three capabilities are, in LeCun's view, the non-negotiable requirements for any system that deserves to be called intelligent. The architecture that has…",
