            "text": "The Core Argument Full autonomy in robotaxis isn't primarily a capability milestone — it's an engineering discipline that requires non-negotiable safety architecture from day one. The companies that treated the first 90% of the problem as the hard part were fundamentally wrong about where the difficulty lives. The last few percentage points of reliability aren't harder versions of the same problem; they require an entirely different architecture, mindset, and timeline. Dmitri Dolgov is co-CEO of Waymo and has been…",
