            "title": "Claude Blog: Built-in memory for Claude Managed Agents",
            "text": "Anthropic launched memory for Claude Managed Agents in public beta. The implementation is filesystem-based — memories are stored as files, giving developers full portability, API management, and audit trails. Memory stores can be scoped by permission level (org-wide read-only vs. per-user read-write), shared across multiple agents concurrently without conflicts, rolled back to earlier versions, and all changes surface in the Claude Console as session events so you can trace what any agent learned and from which se…",
            "link": "https://claude.com/blog/claude-managed-agents-memory"
