            "title": "The MAD Podcast with Matt Turck — OpenAI Board Member Zico Kolter on the Real Risks of Frontier AI",
            "text": "The Takeaway: Safety doesn't scale with capability — you can't just wait for bigger models to become safer, and anyone building AI systems who believes otherwise is taking on risk they haven't priced in. Zico Kolter chairs the Safety and Security Committee on the OpenAI board. He's also the head of the machine learning department at Carnegie Mellon and co-founder of Gray Swan, an AI security company. His vantage point is genuinely unusual: he works on the governance layer above the models and on the attack layer b…",
