            "text": "The Takeaway: Twenty years of persistence — not any single technological breakthrough — is what makes Waymo's lead nearly impossible to replicate. Dmitri Dolgov has been building autonomous vehicles since before most of today's AI founders finished college. He showed up to the DARPA Grand Challenge in 2005 as a grad student, felt what he calls a \"light switch moment,\" and has never looked back. What he's built since — through the Google self-driving car project, through the AV hype cycle and crash, through the lon…",
